1
00:00:13,320 --> 00:00:16,700
After school, the rain comes down

2
00:00:16,780 --> 00:00:20,220
On the window by our seats

3
00:00:20,540 --> 00:00:23,760
You set your bag beside my chair

4
00:00:24,100 --> 00:00:27,200
At our table, table three

5
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:30,540
I draw a line beside my notes

6
00:00:30,620 --> 00:00:34,180
Blue pen moving left to right

7
00:00:34,260 --> 00:00:37,480
You ask what page the homework starts

8
00:00:37,560 --> 00:00:41,120
I say page twelve, then lose my line

9
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:45,600
You write a question in the margin

10
00:00:45,680 --> 00:00:49,000
I write back small and take my time

11
00:00:49,080 --> 00:00:52,320
Your sleeve brushes
my notebook corner

12
00:00:52,400 --> 00:00:56,200
Mine stays close beside your line

13
00:00:56,280 --> 00:00:59,520
Margin notes at table three

14
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:03,060
Blue ink saying stay with me

15
00:01:03,140 --> 00:01:06,180
Rain on glass, our cups half full

16
00:01:06,260 --> 00:01:10,040
Same seat tomorrow after school

17
00:01:10,120 --> 00:01:13,640
Margin notes at table three

18
00:01:13,840 --> 00:01:16,720
One small line from you to me

19
00:01:16,800 --> 00:01:20,100
If we go when the buses roll

20
00:01:20,180 --> 00:01:24,980
Save my seat and I'll walk you home

21
00:01:37,720 --> 00:01:40,760
The cafe clock says almost five

22
00:01:40,840 --> 00:01:44,280
Buses hiss across the lane

23
00:01:44,360 --> 00:01:47,760
You circle words I spelled half wrong

24
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:51,360
I draw a box around your name

25
00:01:51,540 --> 00:01:54,060
You tap your pen against the page

26
00:01:54,140 --> 00:01:58,360
Two soft beats, then let it rest

27
00:01:58,440 --> 00:02:01,420
I try to read the printed part

28
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:05,160
But read your handwriting instead

29
00:02:05,880 --> 00:02:09,220
You fold a corner, I look down

30
00:02:09,300 --> 00:02:12,360
Like I was watching drops of rain

31
00:02:12,440 --> 00:02:16,200
You say tomorrow, same old seat

32
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:20,160
I nod too fast and smile again

33
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:23,660
Margin notes at table three

34
00:02:23,740 --> 00:02:27,280
Blue ink saying stay with me

35
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:30,280
Rain on glass, our cups half full

36
00:02:30,360 --> 00:02:34,100
Same seat tomorrow after school

37
00:02:34,180 --> 00:02:37,640
Margin notes at table three

38
00:02:37,720 --> 00:02:40,660
One small line from you to me

39
00:02:40,740 --> 00:02:44,180
If we go when the buses roll

40
00:02:44,260 --> 00:02:48,980
Save my seat and I'll walk you home

41
00:03:02,200 --> 00:03:05,440
Maybe it starts this quiet

42
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:08,440
With a comma by my name

43
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:12,540
Not a letter, not a promise

44
00:03:12,620 --> 00:03:15,540
Just a page we both can change

45
00:03:15,620 --> 00:03:19,080
No big speech and no loud scene

46
00:03:19,180 --> 00:03:22,360
Only rain and table three

47
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:25,940
You close your book, I pack my pen

48
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:29,400
Then ask to walk you to the street

49
00:03:32,220 --> 00:03:35,620
Margin notes at table three

50
00:03:35,700 --> 00:03:39,000
Blue ink keeping you with me

51
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:42,200
Rain on glass, our cups half full

52
00:03:42,280 --> 00:03:45,980
Same seat tomorrow after school

53
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:49,620
Margin notes at table three

54
00:03:49,880 --> 00:03:52,600
One small line I want to keep

55
00:03:52,680 --> 00:03:56,000
When we go and the buses roll

56
00:03:56,080 --> 00:04:00,860
Save my seat and I'll walk you home

57
00:04:02,260 --> 00:04:07,700
Same seat tomorrow after school

58
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:16,540
Save my seat and I'll walk you home

59
00:04:20,220 --> 00:04:25,500
Same seat tomorrow after school

60
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:44,120
Two lids, one tray

61
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:46,980
Left foot, right foot,
through the doorway

62
00:04:47,060 --> 00:04:49,640
Two lids, one tray

63
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:52,620
We catch our rhythm on the way

64
00:04:52,700 --> 00:04:55,120
Left, right, don't spill

65
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:58,200
Slow down by the door, stand still

66
00:04:58,280 --> 00:05:00,760
Left, right, okay

67
00:05:00,840 --> 00:05:03,860
Two lids, one tray

68
00:05:03,940 --> 00:05:06,380
After class, the counter calls

69
00:05:06,460 --> 00:05:09,080
Two paper straws lean by the wall

70
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:11,440
Two cup lids click into place

71
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:14,680
You make that careful counting face

72
00:05:14,760 --> 00:05:17,440
One tray waits between our hands

73
00:05:17,520 --> 00:05:20,180
Napkin folded like a plan

74
00:05:20,260 --> 00:05:22,920
You say left, I answer right

75
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:26,120
Small steps past the menu light

76
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:31,200
Two lids, one tray

77
00:05:31,280 --> 00:05:34,440
If one cup tips, we pause and wait

78
00:05:34,520 --> 00:05:36,740
Two lids, one tray

79
00:05:36,820 --> 00:05:39,420
Slow and steady, we are okay

80
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:40,360
You say left

81
00:05:40,440 --> 00:05:42,240
I answer right

82
00:05:42,320 --> 00:05:43,140
You say wait

83
00:05:43,220 --> 00:05:44,860
I hold it tight

84
00:05:44,940 --> 00:05:45,940
I say slow

85
00:05:46,020 --> 00:05:47,580
You smile and say

86
00:05:47,660 --> 00:05:49,640
Two lids

87
00:05:49,720 --> 00:06:00,860
One tray

88
00:06:00,940 --> 00:06:03,340
By the side booth, we set them down

89
00:06:03,420 --> 00:06:06,180
Tray edge marks the paper brown

90
00:06:06,260 --> 00:06:08,980
You tear the receipt in two

91
00:06:09,060 --> 00:06:11,720
Write tomorrow, I write me too

92
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:14,460
Your straw taps out a little beat

93
00:06:14,540 --> 00:06:17,240
I move my chair to match your feet

94
00:06:17,320 --> 00:06:19,860
Coats drip softly by the rack

95
00:06:19,940 --> 00:06:22,940
You smile and slide my napkin back

96
00:06:23,020 --> 00:06:26,840
Two lids, one tray

97
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:29,580
Left foot, right foot,
through the doorway

98
00:06:29,660 --> 00:06:32,360
Two lids, one tray

99
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:35,240
We know our rhythm on the way

100
00:06:35,320 --> 00:06:37,680
Two lids, one tray

101
00:06:37,760 --> 00:06:41,040
If one cup tips, we pause and wait

102
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:43,300
Two lids, one tray

103
00:06:43,380 --> 00:06:46,240
Slow and steady, we are okay

104
00:06:46,500 --> 00:06:49,380
Maybe this is how we start

105
00:06:49,460 --> 00:06:52,040
Not too fast and not too far

106
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:54,840
One small task we learn to share

107
00:06:54,920 --> 00:07:01,540
One short walk in cooler air

108
00:07:01,620 --> 00:07:04,320
You take the tray when we stand up

109
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:07,360
I hold the door and almost rush

110
00:07:07,440 --> 00:07:10,060
No big speech and no parade

111
00:07:10,240 --> 00:07:12,820
Just careful steps we take

112
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:15,380
When the crosswalk starts to chime

113
00:07:15,460 --> 00:07:18,340
And the cafe line moves in time

114
00:07:18,420 --> 00:07:21,220
I will listen when you say

115
00:07:21,300 --> 00:07:25,420
Left foot first, then lift the tray

116
00:07:25,500 --> 00:07:30,600
Two lids, one tray

117
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:33,500
Left foot, right foot,
through the doorway

118
00:07:33,580 --> 00:07:36,160
Two lids, one tray

119
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:39,120
We know our rhythm on the way

120
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:41,600
Left, right, don't spill

121
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:44,840
Slow down by the door, stand still

122
00:07:44,940 --> 00:07:47,380
Left, right, okay

123
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:54,680
Two lids, one tray

124
00:07:54,760 --> 00:07:58,260
Left, right, don't spill

125
00:07:58,340 --> 00:08:01,520
Slow down by the door, stand still

126
00:08:01,620 --> 00:08:04,080
Left, right, okay

127
00:08:04,300 --> 00:08:07,120
Two lids, one tray

128
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:31,060
I miss a line on worksheet one

129
00:08:31,140 --> 00:08:34,680
The room hums low, the bell is done

130
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:38,480
My pencil drags a gray mistake

131
00:08:38,560 --> 00:08:42,240
Across the box I meant to make

132
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:47,480
You pass your eraser, palm up slow

133
00:08:47,560 --> 00:08:50,800
A small white boat across the row

134
00:08:50,880 --> 00:08:54,520
I take it like a note with no name

135
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:58,260
And leave one corner free of blame

136
00:08:58,340 --> 00:09:01,940
Borrowed eraser, written name

137
00:09:02,340 --> 00:09:05,400
Blue ink underlined twice

138
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:09,120
Borrowed eraser, written name

139
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:12,700
Shy hello in plain sight

140
00:09:13,100 --> 00:09:17,940
I hand it back by worksheet two

141
00:09:18,020 --> 00:09:21,480
You pencil, “Thanks—are
you good too?”

142
00:09:21,560 --> 00:09:25,140
I circle terms for Friday’s test

143
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:28,660
But read your label like a text

144
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:32,140
The edges wear from every class

145
00:09:32,220 --> 00:09:35,800
Soft crumbs fall near my water glass

146
00:09:35,880 --> 00:09:39,560
You smile and tap the answer line

147
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:43,160
I miss the term but keep your line

148
00:09:43,240 --> 00:09:46,700
Borrowed eraser, written name

149
00:09:46,860 --> 00:09:50,180
Blue ink underlined twice

150
00:09:50,260 --> 00:09:53,280
Borrowed eraser, written name

151
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:57,600
Shy hello in plain sight

152
00:10:10,820 --> 00:10:15,260
I write my answer small today

153
00:10:15,340 --> 00:10:18,980
In pencil dust and folded gray

154
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:22,500
One erased mark on the page

155
00:10:22,580 --> 00:10:25,840
Makes my rushing fingers wait

156
00:10:25,920 --> 00:10:29,520
When last bell clears
the classroom row

157
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:33,100
You zip your bag and move so slow

158
00:10:33,180 --> 00:10:36,920
I match my steps beside your shoes

159
00:10:37,220 --> 00:10:40,480
And ask if I can walk with you

160
00:10:40,620 --> 00:10:44,960
The worksheet slides
beneath my sleeve

161
00:10:45,040 --> 00:10:49,240
One pale square where
marks used to be

162
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:53,040
You pack your books
and check the door

163
00:10:53,360 --> 00:10:56,420
Then pause like you forgot one more

164
00:10:56,500 --> 00:11:00,000
I write my name below the date

165
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:03,420
Slow enough to make you wait

166
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:06,920
You see it there, then turn my way

167
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:10,780
Two quiet names on one clean page

168
00:11:10,860 --> 00:11:14,440
Borrowed eraser, written name

169
00:11:14,520 --> 00:11:17,940
Blue ink underlined twice

170
00:11:18,020 --> 00:11:21,640
Borrowed eraser, written name

171
00:11:21,720 --> 00:11:25,060
Shy hello in plain sight

172
00:11:25,140 --> 00:11:28,200
Borrowed eraser, written name

173
00:11:28,740 --> 00:11:32,140
One clean page, one small sign

174
00:11:32,220 --> 00:11:35,540
Borrowed eraser, written name

175
00:11:35,620 --> 00:11:41,140
Save me a smile next time

176
00:12:06,180 --> 00:12:12,480
After the bell, in
the far left aisle,

177
00:12:12,560 --> 00:12:19,540
spine labels lean in a paper file.

178
00:12:19,620 --> 00:12:25,200
Dust in the blinds
makes narrow lines,

179
00:12:25,280 --> 00:12:32,560
your sleeve brushes
mine; I lose my line.

180
00:12:32,640 --> 00:12:39,980
A book cart squeaks
by the history row,

181
00:12:40,160 --> 00:12:46,960
the wall clock ticks
like it wants to go.

182
00:12:47,040 --> 00:12:51,560
You turn a page with careful hands,

183
00:12:51,640 --> 00:12:57,280
I read where your pencil lands.

184
00:12:58,080 --> 00:13:02,900
Checkout slip at chapter nine,

185
00:13:02,980 --> 00:13:08,910
tucked where the margins meet.

186
00:13:08,990 --> 00:13:11,690
In the quiet place we share,

187
00:13:11,770 --> 00:13:30,070
the page says what we cannot speak.

188
00:13:30,150 --> 00:13:32,870
You slide the book a little near,

189
00:13:32,950 --> 00:13:36,270
point to a sentence underlined clear.

190
00:13:36,350 --> 00:13:39,590
My bookmark waits at chapter nine,

191
00:13:39,670 --> 00:13:42,830
your checkout slip folds over mine.

192
00:13:42,910 --> 00:13:45,930
The pencil zip sounds
loud in the hush,

193
00:13:46,010 --> 00:13:49,170
we both look down, then almost blush.

194
00:13:49,250 --> 00:13:52,450
I start to ask about tomorrow’s rain,

195
00:13:52,530 --> 00:13:57,430
you smile like you heard my name.

196
00:13:58,110 --> 00:14:00,210
“Are you heading out?”

197
00:14:00,290 --> 00:14:02,690
“After this line.”

198
00:14:02,770 --> 00:14:06,370
“The front desk closes soon.”

199
00:14:06,450 --> 00:14:09,490
“We still have time.”

200
00:14:09,570 --> 00:14:12,470
Your thumb keeps place,

201
00:14:12,550 --> 00:14:16,070
my courage turns.

202
00:14:16,150 --> 00:14:18,990
The aisle grows gold,

203
00:14:19,070 --> 00:14:23,390
the last lamp burns.

204
00:14:23,890 --> 00:14:28,030
Checkout slip at chapter nine,

205
00:14:28,110 --> 00:14:31,890
warm as the lights sink low.

206
00:14:31,970 --> 00:14:37,570
You fold the corner next to mine,

207
00:14:37,650 --> 00:14:45,770
we take the slow way home.

208
00:14:45,850 --> 00:14:50,330
Your checkout slip becomes my mark,

209
00:14:50,410 --> 00:14:56,050
between the pages, after dark.

210
00:14:56,130 --> 00:15:00,630
The clock clicks once
by the desk light,

211
00:15:00,710 --> 00:15:06,830
we leave the aisle into the night.

212
00:15:31,120 --> 00:15:36,180
After the library, late in the day,

213
00:15:36,260 --> 00:15:40,580
the cafe bell moves
as our coats sway.

214
00:15:40,660 --> 00:15:44,620
Warm room behind us,
cold street in sight,

215
00:15:44,700 --> 00:15:49,740
your palm leaves a cloud
in the streetlamp light.

216
00:15:49,820 --> 00:15:53,400
You press one finger
and clear a thin lane,

217
00:15:53,480 --> 00:15:58,280
then make a quick face
through the silvered pane.

218
00:15:58,360 --> 00:16:02,800
I laugh too quiet, you grin and stay,

219
00:16:02,880 --> 00:16:07,240
your hand on the handle,
half turned my way.

220
00:16:07,320 --> 00:16:11,040
By the handle, you look back,

221
00:16:11,120 --> 00:16:16,380
I tuck my laugh inside my bag.

222
00:16:16,820 --> 00:16:20,180
Rain taps twice along the frame,

223
00:16:20,260 --> 00:16:25,980
you point outside; I do the same.

224
00:16:26,060 --> 00:16:30,220
You draw an arrow, then wipe it back,

225
00:16:30,300 --> 00:16:34,480
point at my sleeve and make me laugh.

226
00:16:34,560 --> 00:16:38,980
A bus light blinks past
the curb in the rain,

227
00:16:39,060 --> 00:16:43,540
turning our shadows along the lane.

228
00:16:43,620 --> 00:16:48,280
Your sleeve taps mine
by the doorway line,

229
00:16:48,360 --> 00:16:52,900
a tiny joke at closing time.

230
00:16:52,980 --> 00:16:57,180
You ask, "Ready?" I
watch for your sign,

231
00:16:57,260 --> 00:17:01,900
then touch the handle, three in time.

232
00:17:01,980 --> 00:17:03,660
Wait by the glass,

233
00:17:03,740 --> 00:17:05,900
let the cold air pass.

234
00:17:05,980 --> 00:17:07,340
If your breath turns blue,

235
00:17:07,420 --> 00:17:10,420
I can stand there too.

236
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:12,660
One clear line appears,

237
00:17:12,740 --> 00:17:14,960
then the street feels near.

238
00:17:15,040 --> 00:17:16,340
When you nod me through,

239
00:17:16,420 --> 00:17:32,240
I walk out with you.

240
00:17:32,320 --> 00:17:38,440
The room stays warm behind our backs,

241
00:17:38,520 --> 00:17:43,040
cups on the table, books in a stack.

242
00:17:43,120 --> 00:17:47,220
Outside, the buses bend and hiss,

243
00:17:47,300 --> 00:17:51,540
but your slow smile steadies this.

244
00:17:51,620 --> 00:17:56,240
We do not rush the after-school air,

245
00:17:56,320 --> 00:18:00,500
we let the clear line lead us there.

246
00:18:00,580 --> 00:18:05,000
Your hand leaves fog,
my fingers trace,

247
00:18:05,080 --> 00:18:09,720
a clear path across the place.

248
00:18:09,800 --> 00:18:11,580
Wait by the glass,

249
00:18:11,660 --> 00:18:13,800
let the bus lights pass.

250
00:18:13,880 --> 00:18:15,140
One clear line appears,

251
00:18:15,220 --> 00:18:18,600
and the street feels near.

252
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:20,340
You nod me through,

253
00:18:20,420 --> 00:18:22,940
I follow after you.

254
00:18:23,020 --> 00:18:24,400
Your hand mark fades,

255
00:18:24,480 --> 00:18:27,800
but the bright path stays.

256
00:18:27,880 --> 00:18:32,540
One finger clears the glass again,

257
00:18:32,620 --> 00:18:36,720
a thin bright path where we had been.

258
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:42,340
Your hand mark fades,
the street feels near,

259
00:18:42,420 --> 00:18:49,140
the door closes
gently behind us here.

260
00:19:02,640 --> 00:19:06,480
Save the first sip for me

261
00:19:06,560 --> 00:19:09,520
I’ll leave the last taste for you

262
00:19:09,600 --> 00:19:12,980
If the machine gives one can free

263
00:19:13,480 --> 00:19:15,800
We’ll call it our excuse

264
00:19:16,420 --> 00:19:19,880
Peach on the pull-ring shine

265
00:19:20,400 --> 00:19:23,160
Fizz in a careful plan

266
00:19:23,360 --> 00:19:25,860
You grin at row B-four

267
00:19:25,940 --> 00:19:28,400
I reach for the can

268
00:19:29,460 --> 00:19:32,460
Last bell leaves the benches low

269
00:19:32,540 --> 00:19:35,400
Gym shoes squeak on painted floor

270
00:19:35,480 --> 00:19:38,520
You read the snack map row by row

271
00:19:38,600 --> 00:19:41,220
Then stop beside B-four

272
00:19:41,880 --> 00:19:45,160
The peach can sticks,
then drops at last

273
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:48,020
Metal clacks and rolls out fast

274
00:19:48,100 --> 00:19:50,600
I catch it near the rubber seam

275
00:19:50,680 --> 00:20:07,620
You laugh behind the vending machine

276
00:20:07,700 --> 00:20:09,880
You read the flavors out loud

277
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:12,940
Peach, tea, melon cream

278
00:20:13,200 --> 00:20:16,220
I pick the one you almost chose

279
00:20:16,300 --> 00:20:19,320
You say, “That was gonna be me”

280
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:22,120
The can is cold against my sleeve

281
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:25,480
Your straw wrapper curls to the floor

282
00:20:25,680 --> 00:20:28,560
We share it by the practice board

283
00:20:28,880 --> 00:20:31,880
And talk for half a minute more

284
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:37,360
Peach for the joke you tried to hide

285
00:20:37,440 --> 00:20:40,100
Tea for the quiz we both survived

286
00:20:40,640 --> 00:20:43,120
Melon for words kept safe inside

287
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:46,620
Strawberry left on the lower side

288
00:20:46,700 --> 00:20:49,900
The court goes empty past the stairs

289
00:20:49,980 --> 00:20:52,780
Practice whistles thin the air

290
00:20:52,860 --> 00:20:56,180
You ask if peach counts as dinner

291
00:20:56,260 --> 00:20:59,360
I say only if we share

292
00:21:00,220 --> 00:21:03,220
Save the first sip for me

293
00:21:03,300 --> 00:21:06,240
I’ll leave the last taste for you

294
00:21:06,320 --> 00:21:09,840
If the machine gives one can free

295
00:21:10,320 --> 00:21:12,720
We’ll call it our excuse

296
00:21:12,880 --> 00:21:16,460
You press B-four before we go

297
00:21:16,540 --> 00:21:19,940
Not for a drink, just so I know

298
00:21:20,020 --> 00:21:22,400
The empty slot still keeps the place

299
00:21:22,480 --> 00:21:27,300
Of what we chose that day

300
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:46,920
Club table by the bulletin board

301
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:49,780
Markers sorted red and blue

302
00:21:51,040 --> 00:21:53,620
You peel a sticker from the sheet

303
00:21:54,180 --> 00:21:58,940
A green dot lands by room C-three

304
00:21:59,020 --> 00:22:02,140
I check the roster upside down

305
00:22:02,220 --> 00:22:05,860
Trying not to look at you

306
00:22:05,940 --> 00:22:09,580
Your Thursday box has one more mark

307
00:22:09,660 --> 00:22:12,520
Mine gets marked there too

308
00:22:12,740 --> 00:22:18,180
The club chart leans beneath the tape

309
00:22:18,260 --> 00:22:22,040
Your ruler keeps the columns straight

310
00:22:22,120 --> 00:22:25,120
My pencil hovers, then I try

311
00:22:25,200 --> 00:22:29,840
To place my choice beside the date

312
00:22:30,340 --> 00:22:33,720
You say, “Drama crew runs Tuesday”

313
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:37,460
I say, “Photo meets at four”

314
00:22:37,540 --> 00:22:41,380
You move your dot beside mine

315
00:22:41,500 --> 00:22:45,220
Like we found a place for more

316
00:22:59,480 --> 00:23:03,420
At the club table, paper clips

317
00:23:03,520 --> 00:23:07,280
Make silver moons beside the glue

318
00:23:07,360 --> 00:23:11,040
You trade me orange for my blue

319
00:23:11,240 --> 00:23:15,720
Our boxes match before we’re through

320
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:18,620
The room gets louder near the stairs

321
00:23:18,700 --> 00:23:23,540
Announcements blur above the floor

322
00:23:23,620 --> 00:23:27,420
I fold the chart back to your side

323
00:23:27,500 --> 00:23:31,660
You ask, “Are you free at four?”

324
00:23:31,740 --> 00:23:34,740
I thought a calendar was only

325
00:23:34,940 --> 00:23:38,960
Blocks to fill and plans to keep

326
00:23:39,540 --> 00:23:42,780
But your green mark
changed the question

327
00:23:42,860 --> 00:23:46,620
From where to go to who I’ll see

328
00:23:46,760 --> 00:23:50,420
Just a Thursday on the sheet

329
00:23:50,800 --> 00:23:54,400
Written where both of us can see

330
00:23:54,640 --> 00:23:57,580
If our hours overlap

331
00:23:58,600 --> 00:24:01,960
Leave a chair across from me

332
00:24:02,520 --> 00:24:05,560
Our hours overlap

333
00:24:05,940 --> 00:24:09,620
Thursday turns back around

334
00:24:09,960 --> 00:24:13,380
If your dot stays near mine

335
00:24:13,460 --> 00:24:17,360
I’ll stay till the speakers wind down

336
00:24:17,440 --> 00:24:20,620
Our hours overlap

337
00:24:21,020 --> 00:24:25,020
At the club table now

338
00:24:25,100 --> 00:24:29,140
You circle four, I circle back

339
00:24:29,500 --> 00:24:32,660
The green dot writes it down

340
00:24:32,740 --> 00:24:36,460
Green sticker on the chart

341
00:24:36,560 --> 00:24:40,260
One corner lifting by the glue

342
00:24:40,340 --> 00:24:43,840
I pack my marker cap-first

343
00:24:43,920 --> 00:24:50,100
You leave the blue one for me to use

344
00:25:10,300 --> 00:25:12,720
Study lounge when last bell ends

345
00:25:12,800 --> 00:25:14,660
Cushion seam beneath our books

346
00:25:14,740 --> 00:25:17,440
Your pencil case has paper gems

347
00:25:17,520 --> 00:25:19,880
Mine has dates I never look

348
00:25:19,960 --> 00:25:22,480
Battery red at seventeen

349
00:25:22,720 --> 00:25:24,820
Yours is fading fast at nine

350
00:25:24,900 --> 00:25:27,260
You pass the cord across the seat

351
00:25:27,340 --> 00:25:30,040
I pass my workbook down the side

352
00:25:30,120 --> 00:25:32,380
Take the outlet side

353
00:25:32,460 --> 00:25:34,100
I’ll guard the cord

354
00:25:34,600 --> 00:25:36,760
You keep the quiz cards

355
00:25:36,840 --> 00:25:39,140
I’ll clear the board

356
00:25:39,980 --> 00:25:42,560
Half a charge and homework due

357
00:25:42,640 --> 00:25:45,400
Both our screens turn blue

358
00:25:45,480 --> 00:25:47,880
If your phone reaches eighty

359
00:25:47,960 --> 00:25:51,540
Mine can borrow from you

360
00:25:55,040 --> 00:25:57,600
Your vocab cards fall upside down

361
00:25:57,680 --> 00:26:00,140
Past tense, future, wrong and right

362
00:26:00,220 --> 00:26:02,680
I sort the verbs into a stack

363
00:26:02,760 --> 00:26:05,260
You fix my sentence in blue ink

364
00:26:05,340 --> 00:26:07,800
The lounge gets full
by snack-time rush

365
00:26:07,880 --> 00:26:10,280
Chair legs drag across the floor

366
00:26:10,360 --> 00:26:12,460
You angle your screen toward mine

367
00:26:12,540 --> 00:26:15,920
Then hide a laugh behind your sleeve

368
00:26:25,280 --> 00:26:28,240
You wrap the cord around your case

369
00:26:28,320 --> 00:26:30,140
Tuck the plug beneath the flap

370
00:26:30,220 --> 00:26:32,980
I slide my workbook into place

371
00:26:33,060 --> 00:26:35,160
You leave your pencil in the gap

372
00:26:35,240 --> 00:26:38,640
I say, “Your battery’s at eighty”

373
00:26:38,720 --> 00:26:40,540
You say, “Yours can borrow mine”

374
00:26:40,620 --> 00:26:43,460
The charger warms beneath the table

375
00:26:43,540 --> 00:26:45,840
While we pack our bags in time

376
00:26:45,920 --> 00:26:48,280
Take the outlet side

377
00:26:48,360 --> 00:26:49,860
I’ll guard the cord

378
00:26:50,920 --> 00:26:53,500
Half a charge and homework due

379
00:26:53,580 --> 00:26:57,240
Still feels enough with you

380
00:27:24,960 --> 00:27:27,440
Painted stripes before six

381
00:27:27,520 --> 00:27:30,720
Paint still bright beneath our shoes

382
00:27:30,800 --> 00:27:33,560
Your backpack slips again

383
00:27:33,800 --> 00:27:36,400
You laugh and pull it true

384
00:27:36,600 --> 00:27:38,760
The crossing holds us there

385
00:27:38,840 --> 00:27:42,020
With bicycles rolling by

386
00:27:42,260 --> 00:27:44,520
I ask which route you take

387
00:27:44,600 --> 00:27:48,140
You say, “Depends on why”

388
00:27:48,220 --> 00:27:50,640
Shop signs blink awake

389
00:27:50,960 --> 00:27:53,320
Above the awning blue

390
00:27:53,400 --> 00:27:56,140
You hear a far horn bend

391
00:27:56,220 --> 00:27:58,620
I hear it after you

392
00:27:58,840 --> 00:28:01,400
Your notebook bumps your hip

393
00:28:01,480 --> 00:28:04,700
Mine nearly drops again

394
00:28:04,780 --> 00:28:06,800
You catch the strap in time

395
00:28:06,880 --> 00:28:21,600
Then grin like it was planned

396
00:28:21,680 --> 00:28:24,660
People gather at the curb

397
00:28:24,740 --> 00:28:27,280
Then spill across the paint

398
00:28:27,360 --> 00:28:29,620
You keep your pace beside mine

399
00:28:29,700 --> 00:28:32,920
Not early and not late

400
00:28:33,000 --> 00:28:35,580
I had a faster route today

401
00:28:35,660 --> 00:28:38,440
Past the bike racks and the gym

402
00:28:38,520 --> 00:28:41,540
But every shortcut feels too brief

403
00:28:41,620 --> 00:28:44,380
With you still crossing in

404
00:28:44,460 --> 00:28:47,500
You say, “This side is calmer”

405
00:28:47,580 --> 00:28:50,700
I say, “Then I’ll take it too”

406
00:28:50,780 --> 00:28:53,260
The traffic thins behind us

407
00:28:53,340 --> 00:28:55,820
The curb has room for two

408
00:28:55,900 --> 00:28:58,820
Your sleeve brushes my backpack

409
00:28:58,900 --> 00:29:01,640
Your laugh lands near my ear

410
00:29:01,720 --> 00:29:04,320
The other side arrives too soon

411
00:29:04,400 --> 00:29:07,740
But you are still right here

412
00:29:10,720 --> 00:29:12,560
Move when I move

413
00:29:12,640 --> 00:29:15,560
Keep your pace by me

414
00:29:15,640 --> 00:29:18,800
If the crowd pulls forward

415
00:29:18,880 --> 00:29:21,600
Let them pass clean

416
00:29:21,980 --> 00:29:24,320
Cross where I cross

417
00:29:24,620 --> 00:29:27,180
Then choose our side

418
00:29:27,260 --> 00:29:29,620
The short way home can wait

419
00:29:29,700 --> 00:29:34,120
For the longer curbside

420
00:30:14,040 --> 00:30:17,180
Umbrellas crowd the metal rack

421
00:30:17,320 --> 00:30:20,760
Near the side room by the stairs

422
00:30:21,060 --> 00:30:23,320
You shake drops from your sleeve

423
00:30:23,400 --> 00:30:27,740
I find the yellow tag still there

424
00:30:27,960 --> 00:30:30,900
It has a number, half erased

425
00:30:31,640 --> 00:30:34,780
A bent edge from another day

426
00:30:34,860 --> 00:30:38,320
You turn it over, borrow my pen

427
00:30:39,160 --> 00:30:41,520
Then ask what you should say

428
00:30:41,600 --> 00:30:44,000
Tuck it under the elastic

429
00:30:44,200 --> 00:30:47,580
So it doesn’t slip away

430
00:30:48,680 --> 00:30:51,160
Write the table and the hour

431
00:30:51,840 --> 00:30:54,460
For the next review day

432
00:30:55,560 --> 00:30:58,620
Your initials fit above mine

433
00:30:58,900 --> 00:31:02,140
My pen mark crosses through

434
00:31:02,300 --> 00:31:05,140
If we lose each other later

435
00:31:05,680 --> 00:31:08,340
The rack knows what to do

436
00:31:08,760 --> 00:31:13,020
Your umbrella leans on mine

437
00:31:13,100 --> 00:31:16,720
Two handles hooked by accident

438
00:31:17,600 --> 00:31:20,100
I act like I am fixing them

439
00:31:20,720 --> 00:31:24,120
You know exactly what I meant

440
00:31:24,440 --> 00:31:27,380
The notice board is full of tests

441
00:31:27,460 --> 00:31:31,040
Cafeteria noise rolls through

442
00:31:31,120 --> 00:31:35,140
You write, “Study table later?”

443
00:31:35,220 --> 00:31:38,140
I write, “Only if it’s you”

444
00:31:38,220 --> 00:31:40,300
Fold it flat beneath the cover

445
00:31:40,520 --> 00:31:43,860
Keep the number facing out

446
00:31:44,300 --> 00:31:47,380
If the crowd splits us at pickup

447
00:31:47,960 --> 00:31:50,960
We can find the table now

448
00:31:51,340 --> 00:31:54,700
My pen cap stays in your pocket

449
00:31:54,780 --> 00:31:58,560
Your tag rides home with you

450
00:31:58,820 --> 00:32:02,080
The rack keeps one space open

451
00:32:02,160 --> 00:32:04,820
Where our umbrellas used to lean

452
00:32:06,380 --> 00:32:10,020
Weather changes by the hour

453
00:32:10,100 --> 00:32:12,660
Plans get crossed and made again

454
00:32:12,740 --> 00:32:17,180
But a yellow tag is simple

455
00:32:17,260 --> 00:32:20,520
Table, time, and borrowed pen

456
00:32:20,600 --> 00:32:23,880
You tuck it under notebook elastic

457
00:32:24,380 --> 00:32:27,620
Flat against the cover blue

458
00:32:28,080 --> 00:32:31,140
I keep the pen cap by my zipper

459
00:32:32,040 --> 00:32:36,660
Because it came from you

460
00:32:36,920 --> 00:32:40,240
Place it under the elastic

461
00:32:40,440 --> 00:32:44,420
Number facing out

462
00:32:45,320 --> 00:32:48,760
Table, time, and borrowed pen

463
00:32:48,940 --> 00:32:50,800
That’s enough for now

464
00:32:51,920 --> 00:32:54,280
Umbrellas part beside the rack

465
00:32:55,300 --> 00:32:58,360
Your tag rides home in blue

466
00:32:58,700 --> 00:33:02,920
The empty hook leans back

467
00:33:03,100 --> 00:33:06,540
Toward the one I used with you

468
00:33:22,820 --> 00:33:24,960
Quiz key in blue ink

469
00:33:25,040 --> 00:33:27,320
Between your book and mine

470
00:33:27,600 --> 00:33:29,940
Red marks on my answers

471
00:33:30,020 --> 00:33:32,580
Yours look almost fine

472
00:33:33,020 --> 00:33:35,220
You circle question seven

473
00:33:35,680 --> 00:33:37,780
Then slide the sheet my way

474
00:33:37,860 --> 00:33:39,760
I say, “I knew that part”

475
00:33:39,840 --> 00:33:43,160
You say, “Then prove it today”

476
00:33:43,240 --> 00:33:45,400
Show me where I missed it

477
00:33:45,480 --> 00:33:47,680
I’ll try it once again

478
00:33:47,760 --> 00:33:50,020
You read the problem backward

479
00:33:50,100 --> 00:33:53,240
I steal your better pen

480
00:33:53,560 --> 00:33:55,760
If I get the answer

481
00:33:55,840 --> 00:33:58,520
You get half the credit too

482
00:33:58,700 --> 00:34:00,920
Show me where I missed it

483
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:03,700
I learn faster next to you

484
00:34:04,260 --> 00:34:06,460
Cafeteria clatter

485
00:34:06,540 --> 00:34:09,100
Fades behind the math

486
00:34:09,180 --> 00:34:11,620
You split your cookie neatly

487
00:34:11,700 --> 00:34:14,160
And draw a crooked graph

488
00:34:14,240 --> 00:34:16,660
I mix up signs and angles

489
00:34:16,740 --> 00:34:19,300
You laugh but never tease

490
00:34:19,380 --> 00:34:21,940
You say, “Start from the middle”

491
00:34:22,020 --> 00:34:24,620
And suddenly I see

492
00:34:25,020 --> 00:34:26,380
“Is this right?”

493
00:34:26,460 --> 00:34:27,740
“Almost.”

494
00:34:27,820 --> 00:34:28,300
“Again?”

495
00:34:28,380 --> 00:34:28,820
“Try.”

496
00:34:28,900 --> 00:34:29,820
“You’re grinning.”

497
00:34:29,900 --> 00:34:31,100
“So are you.”

498
00:34:31,180 --> 00:34:32,700
“Fine.”

499
00:34:32,780 --> 00:34:35,080
Show me where I missed it

500
00:34:35,160 --> 00:34:37,460
I’ll try it once again

501
00:34:37,640 --> 00:34:39,520
You read the problem backward

502
00:34:39,600 --> 00:34:42,760
I steal your better pen

503
00:34:42,960 --> 00:34:44,700
If I get the answer

504
00:34:44,780 --> 00:34:48,060
You get half the credit too

505
00:34:48,140 --> 00:34:50,360
I may not like the quiz much

506
00:34:50,440 --> 00:34:53,400
But I like studying with you

507
00:34:54,620 --> 00:34:57,220
The answer key gets folded

508
00:34:57,440 --> 00:34:59,820
Inside chapter two

509
00:34:59,900 --> 00:35:02,240
You say we should review it

510
00:35:02,320 --> 00:35:05,080
I say, “If you want to”

511
00:35:05,160 --> 00:35:07,600
The bell has finished ringing

512
00:35:07,720 --> 00:35:10,080
The tables nearly clear

513
00:35:10,160 --> 00:35:12,820
You pack the blue-ink paper

514
00:35:12,900 --> 00:35:16,940
But leave the question here

515
00:35:17,180 --> 00:35:19,480
Show me where I missed it

516
00:35:19,560 --> 00:35:21,920
I’ll try it once again

517
00:35:22,160 --> 00:35:24,840
The answer looks less scary

518
00:35:25,100 --> 00:35:27,300
Written with your pen

519
00:35:27,680 --> 00:35:29,640
If I get the answer

520
00:35:29,720 --> 00:35:32,240
You get half the credit too

521
00:35:32,320 --> 00:35:34,400
I may not like the quiz much

522
00:35:34,480 --> 00:35:37,700
But I like studying with you

523
00:36:05,700 --> 00:36:08,380
Cafeteria clock leans near six

524
00:36:08,460 --> 00:36:11,260
Trays are stacked beside the bins

525
00:36:11,360 --> 00:36:13,600
You collect the empty cups

526
00:36:13,680 --> 00:36:16,880
I gather wrappers, folded in

527
00:36:16,960 --> 00:36:19,620
The main room thins
to chair-leg sounds

528
00:36:19,700 --> 00:36:21,920
Aprons move behind the counter

529
00:36:22,000 --> 00:36:25,340
You ask if I need extra help

530
00:36:25,420 --> 00:36:28,600
I say I found the answer

531
00:36:28,680 --> 00:36:31,160
Put the trays back together

532
00:36:31,880 --> 00:36:33,860
Leave the table clean

533
00:36:33,940 --> 00:36:37,500
If the day has to end here

534
00:36:37,580 --> 00:36:39,920
Keep the space between

535
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:43,240
Not too far, not too formal

536
00:36:43,420 --> 00:36:45,840
Just enough to know

537
00:36:45,920 --> 00:36:48,820
When the clock keeps moving

538
00:36:48,900 --> 00:36:51,680
I still don’t want to go

539
00:36:54,220 --> 00:36:57,000
Your milk carton bends in half

540
00:36:57,080 --> 00:36:59,940
Mine still has a straw inside

541
00:37:00,020 --> 00:37:03,120
You toss the napkins in one shot

542
00:37:03,220 --> 00:37:05,520
I miss and try to hide

543
00:37:05,600 --> 00:37:08,860
You rescue what I dropped

544
00:37:08,940 --> 00:37:11,960
With that look you try to bury

545
00:37:12,040 --> 00:37:14,900
I say, “Nice save,” too late

546
00:37:14,980 --> 00:37:17,920
You say, “Necessary”

547
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:20,340
Put the trays back together

548
00:37:21,180 --> 00:37:23,300
Leave the table clean

549
00:37:23,500 --> 00:37:26,720
If the day has to end here

550
00:37:26,800 --> 00:37:28,960
Keep the space between

551
00:37:29,160 --> 00:37:31,820
Not too far, not too formal

552
00:37:31,900 --> 00:37:34,980
Just enough to know

553
00:37:35,060 --> 00:37:38,020
When the clock keeps moving

554
00:37:38,100 --> 00:38:04,600
I still don’t want to go

555
00:38:04,680 --> 00:38:08,180
Tray Return at 5:59

556
00:38:09,520 --> 00:38:13,760
Silver rail and plastic blue

557
00:38:15,400 --> 00:38:19,820
You push yours beside mine

558
00:38:20,780 --> 00:38:25,440
Like it knows what we should do

559
00:38:26,820 --> 00:38:30,100
The room is almost empty

560
00:38:30,240 --> 00:38:32,540
Our chairs face where we sat

561
00:38:32,620 --> 00:38:37,240
You say, “See you next review”

562
00:38:37,320 --> 00:38:39,860
I carry that

563
00:38:39,960 --> 00:38:42,900
Put the trays back together

564
00:38:43,700 --> 00:38:45,420
Leave the table clean

565
00:38:45,500 --> 00:38:49,080
If the day has to end here

566
00:38:49,160 --> 00:38:52,480
Keep the space between

567
00:39:26,080 --> 00:39:30,020
Courtyard trees drop brown leaves

568
00:39:30,320 --> 00:39:35,580
Onto the bench by our bags

569
00:39:36,000 --> 00:39:40,980
You zip your jacket to your chin

570
00:39:41,680 --> 00:39:46,680
I fix the strap that always drags

571
00:39:46,860 --> 00:39:52,020
The practice field is nearly bare

572
00:39:52,520 --> 00:39:56,700
Shoes squeak past the fence

573
00:39:56,780 --> 00:40:02,320
You tell a story from lunch break

574
00:40:02,720 --> 00:40:09,660
I laugh before it makes sense

575
00:40:09,740 --> 00:40:12,780
We reach the planter by the gate

576
00:40:12,860 --> 00:40:15,680
Pebbles pale around the bed

577
00:40:15,860 --> 00:40:17,860
Your bus route bends away

578
00:40:17,940 --> 00:40:20,820
Mine turns near the bike-rack shed

579
00:40:20,900 --> 00:40:23,380
We both know the parting spot

580
00:40:23,460 --> 00:40:26,300
Before the latch is in view

581
00:40:26,380 --> 00:40:28,920
You check your phone,
then put it back

582
00:40:29,000 --> 00:40:32,320
Like time can wait for you

583
00:40:32,680 --> 00:40:35,120
Blue ink, trays, the yellow tag

584
00:40:35,200 --> 00:40:37,440
Quiz key folded in your bag

585
00:40:37,520 --> 00:40:40,620
All the day’s plain pieces

586
00:40:40,700 --> 00:40:43,420
Gather where the hinges drag

587
00:40:43,500 --> 00:40:46,120
You say, “Don’t forget the graph”

588
00:40:46,200 --> 00:40:48,740
I say, “Don’t lose my pen”

589
00:40:48,820 --> 00:40:50,600
You grin like that is settled

590
00:40:50,680 --> 00:40:54,960
And the latch clicks once again

591
00:41:02,980 --> 00:41:08,460
Latch Click at the Courtyard Gate

592
00:41:08,540 --> 00:41:11,060
Metal note in evening air

593
00:41:11,140 --> 00:41:13,500
You lift two fingers once

594
00:41:13,600 --> 00:41:16,480
I lift mine from over there

595
00:41:16,560 --> 00:41:18,900
The gate rests back in place

596
00:41:19,120 --> 00:41:21,640
Two routes divide in blue

597
00:41:21,720 --> 00:41:25,140
I turn toward home at last

598
00:41:25,840 --> 00:41:28,680
Still thinking about you
